{
  "document_id": "jer-2",
  "title": "Jeremiah 2",
  "type": "scripture",
  "translation": "NRSVue",
  "blocks": [
    {
      "block_id": "jer-2-heading-god-pleads-with-isra",
      "type": "heading",
      "text": "God Pleads with Israel to Repent"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "jer-2-1",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 1,
      "text": "The word of the Lord came to me, saying:"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "jer-2-2",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 2,
      "text": "Go and proclaim in the hearing of Jerusalem, Thus says the Lord:"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "jer-2-3",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 3,
      "text": "Israel was holy to the Lord,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "jer-2-4",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 4,
      "text": "Hear the word of the Lord, O house of Jacob, and all the families of the house of Israel."
    },
    {
      "block_id": "jer-2-5",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 5,
      "text": "Thus says the Lord:"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "jer-2-6",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 6,
      "text": "They did not say, “Where is the Lord,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "jer-2-7",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 7,
      "text": "I brought you into a plentiful land"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "jer-2-8",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 8,
      "text": "The priests did not say, “Where is the Lord?”"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "jer-2-9",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 9,
      "text": "Therefore once more I accuse you,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "jer-2-10",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 10,
      "text": "Cross to the coasts of Cyprus and look;"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "jer-2-11",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 11,
      "text": "Has a nation changed its gods,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "jer-2-12",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 12,
      "text": "Be appalled, O heavens, at this;"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "jer-2-13",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 13,
      "text": "for my people have committed two evils:"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "jer-2-14",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 14,
      "text": "Is Israel a slave? Is he a homeborn servant?"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "jer-2-15",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 15,
      "text": "The lions have roared against him;"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "jer-2-16",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 16,
      "text": "Moreover, the people of Memphis and Tahpanhes"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "jer-2-17",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 17,
      "text": "Have you not brought this upon yourself"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "jer-2-18",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 18,
      "text": "What then do you gain by going to Egypt,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "jer-2-19",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 19,
      "text": "Your wickedness will punish you,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "jer-2-20",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 20,
      "text": "For long ago you broke your yoke"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "jer-2-21",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 21,
      "text": "Yet I planted you as a choice vine"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "jer-2-22",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 22,
      "text": "Though you wash yourself with lye"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "jer-2-23",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 23,
      "text": "How can you say, “I am not defiled;"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "jer-2-24",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 24,
      "text": "a wild ass at home in the wilderness"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "jer-2-25",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 25,
      "text": "Keep your feet from going bare"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "jer-2-26",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 26,
      "text": "As a thief is shamed when caught,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "jer-2-27",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 27,
      "text": "who say to a tree, “You are my father,”"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "jer-2-28",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 28,
      "text": "But where are your gods"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "jer-2-29",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 29,
      "text": "Why do you complain against me?"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "jer-2-30",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 30,
      "text": "In vain I have struck down your children;"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "jer-2-31",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 31,
      "text": "And you, O generation, behold the word of the Lord!"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "jer-2-32",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 32,
      "text": "Can a young woman forget her ornaments"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "jer-2-33",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 33,
      "text": "How well you direct your course"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "jer-2-34",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 34,
      "text": "Also on your skirts is found"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "jer-2-35",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 35,
      "text": "you say, “I am innocent;"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "jer-2-36",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 36,
      "text": "Why do you go about so much"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "jer-2-37",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 37,
      "text": "From there also you will come away"
    }
  ]
}